ill the </div><div class="t m10fe xe h15 y10eb ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">afflictions of this life appear? Verses 17, 18. </div><div class="t m69c x84 h2d yd77 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Notes. </div><div class="t m988 x26 h2d ycd8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m852 x74 h2d y860 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">While this scripture applies especially to ministers of the </div><div class="t m5b5 xe h2d y7d9 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Gospel, it does not exclude others also. The Lord has given to </div><div class="t m268 xe h2d y1283 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">all a part in the work of reconciliation. </div><div class="t m127 x26 h2d yf0a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m325 x74 h2d yf0a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">He who preaches should not only </div><div class="t m1636 x72 h4a yf0a ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">believe </div><div class="t m1717 x9f h2d yf0a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">what he teaches, </div><div class="t m5cb xe h2d y10ad ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">but should conscientiously </div><div class="t m16a8 x1a h4a y10ad ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">practice </div><div class="t mb91 x99 h2d y10ad ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the same.&apos; The most effectual </div><div class="t m12e4 xe h2d y9be ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">way of preaching is by practicing. Rom. 2:21-23. </div><div class="t m6e7 x3e h2d yf44 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot; The teaching of Christ was the expression of an inwrought </div><div class="t mcf6 xe h2d ydff ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">conviction and experience, and those who learn of Him become </div><div class="t m66f xe h2d y1d39 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">teachers after the same divine order. The Word of God, spoken </div><div class="t m3be xe h2d yab0 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by one who is himself sanctified through it, has a life-giving </div><div class="t mac4 xe h2d yd27 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">power that makes it attractive to the hearers, and convicts them </div><div class="t maf2 xe h2d y1470 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that it is 